title: Copper Ion Induced Reactions on Cd-110, Cd-108, Cd-106, Ag-109, Ag-107 and Pd-110. New Rhenium, Osmium and Iridium Isotopes.

x4freetext: Copper Ion Induced Reactions on Cd-110, Cd-108, Cd-106,
Ag-109, Ag-107 and Pd-110. New Rhenium, Osmium and
Iridium Isotopes.
Institut De Physique Nucleaire, Orsay

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zeitschrift fuer Physik A, Hadrons and Nuclei, Vol.287, p.71 (1978)

x4freetext: . Alice Accelerator
Bombardments were Performed with Cu-63 Ions of 400 MeV
Incident Energy. The Beam Intensity was About 2*10**10
Ions/Sec. Thin Ni-Foils were Used to Reduce the
Energy Which was Calculated According to
L.C.Northcliffe Et Al., Nucl.Data A7,233(1970).
According to Measurements of R.Bimbot Et Al., Nucl.
Instr.Meth.153,161(1978) These Calculated Energies are
Too High and Should be Corrected by Some 2 or 3 MeV
Per Each 20 MeV Degradation. Though this Effect was
Known, It was not Corrected For by the Authors, Since
They were Only Interested in Relative Excitation
Functions, Which Should be Wrong by not More Than 2-3
MeV For Neighboring Masses. The Absolute Energies,
However, Might be Too High by Up to 15 MeV in the Low
Energy Region (COMMENT BY THE COMPILER OF KACHAPAG).
The Identification of the Mostly Unknown Alpha-Emitting
Product Nuclides was Performed on the Basis of Shape
And Position of the Excitation Functions, Cross
Bombardment of Several Neighboring Targets, and Alpha
Energy-Systematics.
The Main Purpose of this Work was a Search For New
Isotopes and not the Measurement of Cross-Sections.
Therefore, Only Relative Yields are Given, not
Corrected For the Mostly Unknown Alpha-Branchings.
The Energies Given are Increasingly Incorrect with
Decreasing Energy, See Under Method.
Information About Errors is Missing
Alpha-Energies and Half-Lives For Several
Unknown Isotopes are Presented.
Lakw
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Last checking has been done.
Alpha Decay Only.
